No availability date yet, but the video has been posted on HP’s ...";s:7:"blog_id";s:13:"absolutegeeks";s:14:"post_timestamp";i:1398691800;s:12:"post_content";s:1028:"<p>Meet the HP Slatebook 14, a laptop running Android.</p>
<p>No availability date yet, but the video has been posted on HP’s video page, so it’s safe to assume that it’s the real thing. Full specs aren’t available yet also, however, the video reviles the main specs.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.absolutegeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Screen-Shot-2014-04-28-at-17.17.26.png"><img src="webkit-fake-url://e29c4f89-0c63-4c27-9afa-ff6decc6daf5/image.tiff" alt=""></a></p>
<p>HP Slatebook 14 will have a 14-inch full HD touchscreen with a microSD card slot, HDMI port, 3 USB ports, and audio jack. The keyboard is the same you’d find on a normal laptop, but with some additional keys specifically for Android.</p>
<p><span>The body seems to be made of polycarbonate, which hints to an affordable device, though we shouldn’t expect anything too cheap. </span></p>
