<p>This is Microsoft’s first marketing attempt after the acquisition with its own branding used. It’ll be interesting to see where the company goes with its message.</p>";s:17:"post_image_height";i:360;s:16:"post_image_width";i:480;s:11:"post_visits";i:8;s:18:"post_twitterShares";i:4;s:19:"post_facebookShares";i:1;s:16:"post_totalShares";i:5;s:16:"post_socialScore";i:15;s:13:"post_virality";i:13;s:9:"blog_name";s:14:"Absolute Geeks";s:16:"blog_description";s:28:"Unleash The Tech Geek In You";s:8:"blog_url";s:24:"http://absolutegeeks.com";s:11:"blog_author";s:0:"";s:28:"blog_author_twitter_username";s:13:"absolutegeeks";s:13:"blog_rss_feed";s:34:"http://www.absolutegeeks.com/feed/";s:9:"blog_tags";s:4:"tech";s:2:"id";i:268;s:11:"blog_active";i:1;s:24:"blog_last_post_timestamp";i:1401602040;}i:8;O:8:"stdClass":26:{s:7:"post_id";i:28608;s:8:"post_url";s:98:"http://lfadi.wordpress.com/2014/04/28/woman-transformed-into-a-slice-of-pepperoni-pizza-photoshop/";s:10:"post_title";s:63:"Woman transformed into a slice of pepperoni pizza – Photoshop";s:10:"post_image";s:43:"http://img.youtube.com/vi/Hnvoz91k8hc/0.jpg";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:7:"blog_id";s:5:"lfadi";s:14:"post_timestamp";i:1398672480;s:12:"post_content";s:574:"<p><span><iframe type="text/html" width="700" height="424" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/Hnvoz91k8hc?version=3&rel=1&fs=1&showsearch=0&showinfo=1&iv_load_policy=1&wmode=transparent" frameborder="0"></iframe></span></p><br><a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/lfadi.wordpress.com/2628/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/lfadi.wordpress.com/2628/"></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=lfadi.wordpress.com&blog=44253098&post=2628&subd=lfadi&ref=&feed=1" width="1" height="1">";s:17:"post_image_height";i:360;s:16:"post_image_width";i:480;s:11:"post_visits";i:22;s:18:"post_twitterShares";i:1;s:19:"post_facebookShares";i:2;s:16:"post_totalShares";i:3;s:16:"post_s